    'terms_h3' => 'Currency conversion statement',
    'terms_h3p1' => 'All payments will be effected in Serbian currency – dinar (RSD). The amount your credit card account will be charged for is obtained through the conversion of the price in Euro into Serbian dinar according to the current exchange rate of the Serbian National Bank. When charging your credit card, the same amount is converted into your local currency according to the exchange rate of credit card associations. As a result of this conversion there is a possibility of a slight difference from the original price stated in our web site.',

    'terms_h4' => 'VAT Statement',
    'terms_h4p1' => 'VAT is included in the price and there are no hidden costs.',

    'terms_h5' => 'Conditions of use',
    'terms_h5p1' => 'Webglobe Company (hereinafter referred to as Webglobe) is a provider of Wireless Internet, Web Hosting, Internet domain registration and server leasing to natural persons and companies. (hereinafter: the User). Webglobe reserves the right to deny service to the User in case the use of the same does not comply with the terms of use. Webglobe is committed to enabling Customer to use the services in the best possible way, including server work, customer support and system troubleshooting. The user uses our services at his own risk. Webglobe gives no warranty and is not liable for the damage it may suffer using the Service. Hosting service users (web hosting, VPS servers, dedicated servers, server housing) are not authorized to resell services to third parties unless this is defined by a contract. The User is obliged to act in accordance with the terms of use prescribed by Webglobe, to regularly settle his obligations, to regularly inform us of the change of his personal/company information with which he has purchased one of our services. In case of unauthorized ise of service, the user is obliged to notify Webglobe.',

    'terms_h6' => 'Contract validity',
    'terms_h6p1' => 'The contract is valid until some of the parties (User or Webglobe) terminate the cooperation or contract. The user can terminate the contract when it suits him. The user who buys any service agrees with the terms of use. The services provided by Webglobe are time-limited and Webglobe is not obligated to refund the paid order if the user terminates the cooperation.',

